new america's public interest technology fellowship program is an ambitious new initiative designed to support an emerging public interest technology sector in americathe application of technology knowledge skill in policy-making and public service to help solve public problem just a public interest law became an esteemed public service career path a generation ago we believe public interest technologist are critical to our future prosperity a a nation
what do we mean by public interest technologist we cast a wide net our goal with the public interest technology fellowship is to find bold thinker that want to join the work of building an ecosystem of engineer data scientist software developer lawyer economist and organizer that are all engaged in the common work of harnessing the power of technology to solve public problem public interest technology is not simply about building digital system and service it is about tackling policy challenge that are directly about technology or shaped by technological change and it is about making the type of innovative approach to management organization and problem solving that are emblematic of the technology community available to those seeking to make or influence policy at every level
we will have two round of application for public interest technology fellowships the application deadline is march 15 2017
through this initiative fellow will advance big idea in public interest technology in a variety of way proposals can be for a short-term or part-time project 3-9 month or they can be for longer term full-time and in depth programmatic work 12-18 month we envision a broad typology of project that includes but is not limited to these example
exit fellowship a project for technologist leaving public service designed to document lesson learned analyze challenge articulate aspiration and offer training for the next cohort of public interest technologist
parallel public service a project designed to work in parallel on a technology issue policy system or service that is currently before governmentworking with the relevant institution to test idea develop new thinking organizing partner and help deliver better outcome
community technology a project that experiment with leveraging technology to address a particular community need at the local level by convening discussion and planning documenting a proposal and working with community stakeholder to design and implement a pilot project
data-driven policy a project designed to build new or leverage existing data set to apply new method of data science to public policy problem
innovation and management a project that look at how to change management practice in public institution to better attract retain and empower technologist and innovative thinker
with these project and fellowship we seek to establish an ecosystem of public interest technology practice to grow it capacity to document it learning both inside and outside government and to test different form of implementing technology-driven solution to public problem at the local state and national level
fellows benefit from a financial stipend engagement with each other and with new america's various policy program and the expanded audience and exposure from new america and it medium partner fellows are encouraged to work with new america's national networkincluding our team in new york chicago and the bay areathough a residency in dc is preferred precise term and stipend level of fellowship vary widely according to project type duration and level of experience
